23
00:05:38,932 --> 00:05:40,001
Jesus.

24
00:05:40,092 --> 00:05:42,481
Bob, what button did you push?

25
00:05:49,012 --> 00:05:51,242
(sirens)

26
00:06:12,972 --> 00:06:17,841
(police radio) All responding
"David Team" units respond to lot 11.

27
00:06:26,772 --> 00:06:28,842
Mr Bagwell,
make sure these other elevators...

28
00:06:28,932 --> 00:06:30,490
..remain locked down and empty.

29
00:06:30,572 --> 00:06:31,129
Yes, sir.

30
00:06:31,212 --> 00:06:33,726
There's no other way... no doors...
no other way in or out...

31
00:06:33,812 --> 00:06:35,131
..except through access panels,
is that correct?

32
00:06:35,212 --> 00:06:35,849
Yes, sir.

33
00:06:35,932 --> 00:06:39,368
Gentlemen, what we have here
are 13 passengers in an express elevator...

34
00:06:39,452 --> 00:06:40,726
..below floor 30.

35
00:06:41,972 --> 00:06:43,564
The bomb's already taken out cables.

36
00:06:43,652 --> 00:06:46,086
The bomber wants $3 million
or he blows the emergency brakes.

37
00:06:46,172 --> 00:06:47,571
What's our clock?

38
00:06:47,652 --> 00:06:49,051
He gave one hour.

39
00:06:49,132 --> 00:06:52,204
That leaves us 23 minutes exactly.

40
00:06:52,292 --> 00:06:54,601
Anything else
that'll keep this elevator from falling?

41
00:06:54,692 --> 00:06:55,568
The basement.

42
00:06:55,652 --> 00:06:57,404
The city would like to avoid that event,
Officer Traven.

43
00:06:57,492 --> 00:06:59,050
