00:08:01,892 --> 00:08:04,167
(drilling)

65
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:05,727
Hello!

66
00:08:05,812 --> 00:08:08,724
Come on, man. Get us out of here!

67
00:08:09,172 --> 00:08:10,321
Hello!

68
00:08:12,652 --> 00:08:14,244
Please, help us!

69
00:08:15,332 --> 00:08:16,731
Come on, man!

70
00:08:20,092 --> 00:08:21,411
(drilling)

71
00:08:26,692 --> 00:08:29,445
(drilling)

72
00:08:41,892 --> 00:08:43,166
Help!

73
00:08:43,252 --> 00:08:46,210
Please, get us out of here!

74
00:08:46,292 --> 00:08:47,407
Please!

75
00:09:09,412 --> 00:09:10,845
Please!

76
00:09:10,932 --> 00:09:12,809
Get us out of here!

77
00:09:14,292 --> 00:09:15,805
Who's up there?

78
00:09:16,492 --> 00:09:17,481
Who's up there?

79
00:09:18,212 --> 00:09:19,201
What's going on?

80
00:09:19,292 --> 00:09:21,886
Ladies and gentlemen, this is the LAPD.

81
00:09:21,972 --> 00:09:24,281
- Thank God.
- What are you doing up there?

82
00:09:24,372 --> 00:09:28,570
(Traven) There's been
an elevator malfunction, so just relax.

83
00:09:28,692 --> 00:09:32,446
Hey, come on!
What are you guys waiting for?

84
00:09:32,532 --> 00:09:34,807
We'll have you out of there
as soon as possible.

85
00:09:35,772 --> 00:09:36,727
Am I lying?

86
00:09:37,892 --> 00:09:39,371
How come they sent cops here?

87
00:09:39,452 --> 00:09:41,488
Shouldn't they send repair guys?

88
00:09:41,572 --> 00:09:43,164
- Yeah.
- Makes no sense.

89
00:09:50,292 --> 00:09:51,361
What do you think?

90
00:09:53,172 --> 00:09:55,003
You're the expert. I just work here.

91
00:09:55,092 --> 00:09:56,764
Looks pretty solid.

92
00:09:56,852 --> 00:09:58,604
Anyone we know?

93
00:09:58,692 --> 00:10:01,411
I don't recognise the work, but he's a pro.

94
00:10:01,492 --> 00:10:03,722
He's cutting it close.

95
00:10:03,812 --> 00:10:05,131
I don't like it.

96
00:10:05,212 --> 00:10:06,691
Well, what's to like?

97
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:08,569
Mac said we hold, so we hold.

98
00:10:17,412 --> 00:10:19,801
All right. Pop quiz.

99
00:10:19,892 --> 00:10:21,245
The airport. Gunman with one hostage.

100
00:10:21,332 --> 00:10:24,130
He's using her for cover.
He's almost to a plane.

101
00:10:24,212 --> 00:10:26,680
You're 100 feet away.

102
00:10:32,772 --> 00:10:33,488
Jack.

103
00:10:35,372 --> 00:10:36,885
Shoot the hostage.

104
00:10:37,812 --> 00:10:38,722
What?

105
00:10:38,812 --> 00:10:40,370
Take her out of the equation.

106
00:10:40,452 --> 00:10:42,682
Go for the good wound.
He can't get to the plane with her.

107
00:10:43,892 --> 00:10:44,642
Clear shot.

108
00:10:44,732 --> 00:10:46,643
You're deeply nuts. You know that?

109
00:10:46,732 --> 00:10:49,565
"Shoot the hostage." (laughs)

110
00:10:51,452 --> 00:10:53,761
Harry, this is wrong.

111
00:10:53,852 --> 00:10:56,161
He's going to blow it anyway.

112
00:10:56,252 --> 00:10:57,321
Why?

113
00:10:57,412 --> 00:10:59,880
I don't know. Gut feeling.

114
00:10:59,972 --> 00:11:03,044
Right now, Mac outranks your gut, so we sit.

115
00:11:03,132 --> 00:11:05,521
This is taking way too long.

116
00:11:06,892 --> 00:11:09,611
How much you think that elevator weights?

117
00:11:09,692 --> 00:11:11,284
Jack, come on.

118
00:11:12,892 --> 00:11:15,884
Maybe we can do something
about those hostages.

119
00:11:17,012 --> 00:11:19,401
We're not going to shoot them, right?

120
00:11:20,412 --> 00:11:22,721
Hey, where you going?

121
00:11:22,812 --> 00:11:24,211
What's going on?

122
00:11:25,212 --> 00:11:27,009
Don't go!

123
00:11:27,092 --> 00:11:28,605
Don't leave us here!

124
00:11:42,092 --> 00:11:45,129
No, we just take them out of the equation.

125
00:12:17,332 --> 00:12:18,651
Are you sure it'll hold?

126
00:12:18,732 --> 00:12:20,085
It'll hold.

127
00:12:21,732 --> 00:12:23,006
Six minutes.

128
00:12:24,172 --> 00:12:26,049
I can't get any more time.

129
00:12:26,132 --> 00:12:27,451
He's not talking!

130
00:12:27,532 --> 00:12:29,682
I need the goddamn money now.

131
00:12:38,212 --> 00:12:42,285
Tell me again, Harry. Why did I take this job?

132
00:12:42,372 --> 00:12:43,771
Aw, come on. 30 more years of this,...

133
00:12:43,852 --> 00:12:46,685
..you get a tiny pension
and a cheap gold watch.

134
00:12:46,772 --> 00:12:47,682
Cool.

135
00:12:48,292 --> 00:12:49,042
Ho.

136
00:13:19,052 --> 00:13:21,407
God, it's hot in here.

137
00:13:21,492 --> 00:13:22,607
There's no air.

138
00:13:22,692 --> 00:13:24,410
Can't they just pry the doors open?

139
00:13:24,492 --> 00:13:25,527
I can't breathe.

140
00:13:30,532 --> 00:13:32,921
Don't fuck with daddy.

141
00:13:38,972 --> 00:13:40,166
(screaming)

142
00:14:01,172 --> 00:14:03,970
Grab her hand! Grab her hand!

143
00:14:05,372 --> 00:14:07,681
Usually they fall down now.

144
00:14:07,772 --> 00:14:08,887
Oh, my God!

145
00:14:13,132 --> 00:14:14,485
Get her out of there!

146
00:14:16,292 --> 00:14:19,011
He's early! Son of a bitch is early!

147
00:14:37,532 --> 00:14:39,762
Mac, we need more help up here now!

148
00:14:40,572 --> 00:14:41,561
Oh, please!

149
00:14:42,012 --> 00:14:43,809
I don't want to die!

150
00:14:43,892 --> 00:14:45,325
Please save us!

151
00:14:50,932 --> 00:14:52,331
Open the door!

152
00:14:54,652 --> 00:14:55,528
Open the doors!

153
00:14:55,612 --> 00:14:56,442
Help!

154
00:14:57,172 --> 00:14:58,491
Please help me!

155
00:14:58,572 --> 00:14:59,766
Get me out!

156
00:14:59,852 --> 00:15:01,001
We'll get you out!

157
00:15:01,092 --> 00:15:03,083
Come on. Give me your hands!

158
00:15:03,172 --> 00:15:05,891
It's OK, give me your hands.

159
00:15:13,972 --> 00:15:15,291
Watch your head.

160
00:15:15,452 --> 00:15:16,885
OK, I've got you.

161
00:15:17,412 --> 00:15:18,162
Take it easy.

162
00:15:18,252 --> 00:15:19,890
- Oh, thank you.
- You're fine.

163
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:21,890
- You're fine.
- Thank you.

164
00:15:21,972 --> 00:15:23,690
Take her. Let's go. Who's next?

165
00:15:26,772 --> 00:15:27,807
Thank you.

166
00:15:28,932 --> 00:15:29,842
We've got you, ma'am.

167
00:15:36,532 --> 00:15:38,329
What the hell is all this?

168
00:15:38,412 --> 00:15:39,970
Help us! Hurry!

169
00:15:42,532 --> 00:15:44,841
Hurry, hurry! Let's go! Go! Go!

170
00:15:44,932 --> 00:15:45,887
Let's go!

171
00:15:45,972 --> 00:15:47,644
Come on. Come on.

172
00:15:52,332 --> 00:15:54,892
Oh, my God!

173
00:15:54,972 --> 00:15:56,041
Help me out!

174
00:15:56,132 --> 00:15:57,201
Please, help me out.

175
00:15:59,252 --> 00:16:00,241
Come on, lady! Come on!

176
00:16:00,332 --> 00:16:01,651
No. No.

177
00:16:01,732 --> 00:16:03,051
Come on, lady! Come on!

178
00:16:03,132 --> 00:16:04,485
Grab my hand!

179
00:16:08,572 --> 00:16:09,641
Come on!

180
00:16:09,732 --> 00:16:10,642
Let's go! It's going to fall!

181
00:16:10,732 --> 00:16:11,881
No! I can't!

182
00:16:13,292 --> 00:16:16,170
Just take one step, reach out,
and take my hand.

183
00:16:16,252 --> 00:16:17,207
Come on!

184
00:16:18,452 --> 00:16:19,521
Come on!

185
00:16:21,652 --> 00:16:23,051
Oh! Oh, God!

186
00:16:23,132 --> 00:16:25,168
Don't let go of me.

187
00:16:25,252 --> 00:16:26,287
You're OK.

188
00:16:38,012 --> 00:16:39,047
(crash)

189
00:16:41,252 --> 00:16:42,571
My... my shoe!

190
00:16:42,652 --> 00:16:44,324
Let's go! Let's go!

191
00:16:45,532 --> 00:16:46,885
Was it good for you?

192
00:16:46,972 --> 00:16:50,089
It was great for me.
How was it for you, honey?

193
00:16:50,172 --> 00:16:51,605
Elevator dropped.

194
00:16:51,692 --> 00:16:54,286
Oh, good. That's good to know.

195
00:16:55,332 --> 00:16:56,481
(sigh)

196
00:16:58,972 --> 00:17:00,371
Is your watch slow?

197
00:17:00,452 --> 00:17:03,603
Uh-uh. He jumped the gun.
We had three minutes left.

198
00:17:03,692 --> 00:17:05,648
Why does he do that?

199
00:17:05,732 --> 00:17:07,563
He's losing his $3 million.

200
00:17:07,652 --> 00:17:10,450
I don't know. Maybe he couldn't
hold his wad long enough.

201
00:17:10,532 --> 00:17:13,365
It's a common problem
among middle-aged men.

202
00:17:13,452 --> 00:17:14,851
So I'm told.

203
00:17:19,572 --> 00:17:20,925
He's here.

204
00:17:21,012 --> 00:17:22,491
He could've blown that thing from Pacoima.

205
00:17:23,932 --> 00:17:26,765
No. He knew we were up to something.

206
00:17:26,852 --> 00:17:28,205
He's close by.

207
00:17:28,292 --> 00:17:30,806
He's not going to corner
himself in a building...

208
00:17:30,892 --> 00:17:33,725
...we evacuated anyway. Come on.

209
00:17:39,252 --> 00:17:42,403
He'd want to be here,
but he'd want to stay mobile.

210
00:17:42,492 --> 00:17:43,641
Right?

211
00:17:47,332 --> 00:17:48,651
The elevators.

212
00:17:48,732 --> 00:17:51,690
Passenger cars were stopped.
They checked them out.

213
00:17:51,772 --> 00:17:53,683
What about the freight elevators?

214
00:18:14,612 --> 00:18:15,931
(coughing)

215
00:18:17,012 --> 00:18:19,810
Will the mystery guest please sign in?

216
00:18:19,892 --> 00:18:20,563
What?

217
00:18:23,132 --> 00:18:23,962
Jack!

218
00:18:25,092 --> 00:18:26,207
Damn it.

219
00:19:01,892 --> 00:19:03,245
(gunshot)

220
00:19:06,012 --> 00:19:07,809
Get to the side!

221
00:19:17,652 --> 00:19:19,244
(moaning)

222
00:19:23,212 --> 00:19:25,646
Shit! Shit! Shit!

223
00:19:27,612 --> 00:19:29,682
Up! Get your ass up!

224
00:19:29,772 --> 00:19:31,649
(groaning)

225
00:20:10,932 --> 00:20:14,083
I don't suppose anybody
will give me 3 million...

226
00:20:14,172 --> 00:20:16,003
..just for you.

227
00:20:16,292 --> 00:20:16,804
(click)

228
00:20:20,812 --> 00:20:22,530
Hold it!

229
00:20:24,132 --> 00:20:25,531
Pop quiz, hotshot.

230
00:20:27,132 --> 00:20:28,611
Terrorist holding a police hostage.

231
00:20:28,692 --> 00:20:30,489
Got enough dynamite
strapped to his chest...

232
00:20:30,572 --> 00:20:32,608
..to blow a building in half.
Now, what do you do?

233
00:20:32,692 --> 00:20:36,401
There's gonna be 50 cops
waiting for you in the basement.

234
00:20:36,492 --> 00:20:38,847
Standard flanking deployment, right?

235
00:20:38,932 --> 00:20:41,571
Maybe we'll get off on the third floor, huh?

236
00:20:44,092 --> 00:20:46,367
At least that's what they'll think.

237
00:20:46,452 --> 00:20:48,522
I want a location on those goddamn shots!

238
00:20:48,612 --> 00:20:50,568
Briggs! Where's Jack and Harry?

239
00:20:50,652 --> 00:20:52,210
Lieutenant, we've got movement...

240
00:20:52,292 --> 00:20:53,361
..on the freight elevator.

241
00:21:00,212 --> 00:21:01,884
It's on three. Let's move!

242
00:21:01,972 --> 00:21:03,405
(elevator bell dings)

243
00:21:03,732 --> 00:21:05,643
End of the line.

244
00:21:05,732 --> 00:21:09,725
This day has been real disappointing,
I don't mind saying.

245
00:21:09,812 --> 00:21:11,165
Why?
Because you didn't get to kill everyone?

246
00:21:11,252 --> 00:21:14,767
There'll come a time, boy,
when you'll wish you never met me.

247
00:21:14,852 --> 00:21:17,082
Mister, I'm already there.

248
00:21:17,172 --> 00:21:18,730
You can see I'm in charge here.

249
00:21:18,812 --> 00:21:19,642
I drop this stick...

250
00:21:19,732 --> 00:21:23,202
...and they pick your friend up
with a sponge.

251
00:21:23,852 --> 00:21:25,444
Are you ready to die, friend?

252
00:21:25,532 --> 00:21:26,248
Fuck you.

253
00:21:26,332 --> 00:21:28,926
In 200 years, we've come from...

254
00:21:29,012 --> 00:21:32,163
..."I regret but I have one life to give
for my country"...

255
00:21:32,252 --> 00:21:33,367
...to "fuck you"?

256
00:21:33,452 --> 00:21:35,204
Go ahead. Drop the stick. Do it.

257
00:21:35,292 --> 00:21:36,247
Shut up, Harry.

258
00:21:36,332 --> 00:21:39,369
We've got all the balls
in the world here, man.

259
00:21:39,452 --> 00:21:41,522
Give it up. You got nowhere to go!

260
00:21:42,532 --> 00:21:44,090
Shoot the hostage.

261
00:21:47,092 --> 00:21:48,320
Say goodbye, Harry.

262
00:21:48,412 --> 00:21:50,004
(groans)

263
00:21:53,332 --> 00:21:54,731
You fuck!

264
00:21:57,252 --> 00:21:58,241
Freeze!

265
00:22:00,052 --> 00:22:01,371
Freeze!

266
00:22:01,452 --> 00:22:04,285
Give it up! You're out of options!

267
00:22:24,052 --> 00:22:25,246
(applause)

268
00:22:26,652 --> 00:22:28,563
Through dedication and bravery,...

269
00:22:28,652 --> 00:22:31,371
..these next two officers
effected the rescue...

270
00:22:31,452 --> 00:22:33,329
..of 13 citizens of this city.

271
00:22:33,412 --> 00:22:35,403
And thanks to them,..

272
00:22:35,492 --> 00:22:38,211
..the only life taken
by the terrorist's bomb, was his own.

273
00:22:38,292 --> 00:22:41,011
You shot me. I can't believe it.

274
00:22:41,092 --> 00:22:44,164
They're giving you a medal
