01:19:32,996 --> 01:19:34,315
Jack, please.

1366
01:19:39,516 --> 01:19:40,187
OK?

1367
01:19:40,596 --> 01:19:41,472
Please?

1368
01:19:41,556 --> 01:19:42,466
All right?

1369
01:19:47,596 --> 01:19:48,915
We're going to die.

1370
01:19:48,996 --> 01:19:51,669
No, we're not. We got this far, OK?

1371
01:20:13,156 --> 01:20:14,794
I'll be damned.

1372
01:20:18,756 --> 01:20:19,427
Did you go to the...

1373
01:20:19,516 --> 01:20:22,076
...University of Arizona?

1374
01:20:22,156 --> 01:20:23,032
Yeah? So?

1375
01:20:23,116 --> 01:20:24,390
Good football team.

1376
01:20:24,476 --> 01:20:26,512
Yeah, I guess so.

1377
01:20:26,596 --> 01:20:28,029
I don't really know.

1378
01:20:28,116 --> 01:20:29,868
Arizona Wildcats.

1379
01:20:31,596 --> 01:20:32,426
Right.

1380
01:20:32,516 --> 01:20:34,268
He can see you.

1381
01:20:34,356 --> 01:20:35,914
What?

1382
01:20:35,996 --> 01:20:38,112
He can see you.

1383
01:20:38,196 --> 01:20:40,107
Just keep looking straight ahead.

1384
01:20:54,916 --> 01:20:58,431
He called you a wildcat before.
I didn't even pick up on it.

1385
01:20:58,516 --> 01:20:59,949
Bastard's got a camera
right in your face.

1386
01:21:00,036 --> 01:21:00,946
He can see the whole bus.

1387
01:21:01,036 --> 01:21:02,947
He's been playing me from minute one.

1388
01:21:03,036 --> 01:21:04,913
Well, he can see me,
but can he hear me?

1389
01:21:04,996 --> 01:21:07,271
Doesn't look like it.
He's just watching.

1390
01:21:12,556 --> 01:21:14,911
(TV) A citybus rigged to explode
if it slows down...

1391
01:21:14,996 --> 01:21:18,352
..races around literally in circles
at the Los Angeles airport.

1392
01:21:18,436 --> 01:21:20,745
The two dead are a female passenger
and the driver...

1393
01:21:20,836 --> 01:21:23,669
..of another bus,
both blown up by the bomber.

1394
01:21:23,756 --> 01:21:26,224
The other people in jeopardy are, of course,
the passengers of the bus,...

1395
01:21:26,316 --> 01:21:28,227
..held hostage at the whim of a mad man.

1396
01:21:31,036 --> 01:21:33,630
"The whim of a madman."

1397
01:21:33,716 --> 01:21:35,069
I like that.

1398
01:21:35,156 --> 01:21:39,069
There's a camera on the bus
just over my left shoulder.

1399
01:21:39,156 --> 01:21:40,669
I want you to stare...

1400
01:21:40,756 --> 01:21:41,666
..straight ahead.

1401
01:21:42,036 --> 01:21:45,426
Don't make any big movements, OK?

1402
01:21:46,916 --> 01:21:47,826
It's Jack.

1403
01:21:47,916 --> 01:21:50,225
Yeah, I know about Harry.

1404
01:21:52,756 --> 01:21:54,986
Is that news van still around?

1405
01:21:55,076 --> 01:21:57,306
Get those cameras to stop taping.

1406
01:21:58,796 --> 01:22:00,115
LAPD. I need this unit.

1407
01:22:00,196 --> 01:22:01,515
You can broadcast UHF, right?

1408
01:22:01,596 --> 01:22:02,426
Yeah, sure.

1409
01:22:02,516 --> 01:22:04,108
There's a signal going to that bus.

1410
01:22:04,196 --> 01:22:05,595
I want you to find it.

1411
01:22:06,316 --> 01:22:08,671
(officer) Emergency.
We have to take you off the air.

1412
01:22:08,756 --> 01:22:10,348
Please, sir, stop taping.

1413
01:22:10,436 --> 01:22:11,312
Come on.

1414
01:22:11,396 --> 01:22:14,194
Come on. Good! Tape off of that.

1415
01:22:17,076 --> 01:22:21,035
Remember, no big movements.
Just look whipped.

1416
01:22:21,116 --> 01:22:23,584
That ain't gonna be too hard.

1417
01:22:34,636 --> 01:22:35,751
Tape it. Good. Come on. Tape it.

1418
01:22:35,836 --> 01:22:37,394
It's taping!

1419
01:22:47,316 --> 01:22:48,192
Jack.

1420
01:22:48,276 --> 01:22:49,072
Yeah?

1421
01:22:49,156 --> 01:22:50,066
Look.

1422
01:22:53,836 --> 01:22:55,269
Mac, fuel.

1423
01:22:55,356 --> 01:22:57,153
Jack, five minutes.

1424
01:22:57,236 --> 01:22:58,794
Not enough time. Run the tape.

1425
01:22:58,876 --> 01:22:59,945
We have to unload.

1426
01:23:00,036 --> 01:23:01,913
I only have a minute of tape.

1427
01:23:01,996 --> 01:23:02,826
Do it now.

1428
01:23:02,916 --> 01:23:06,591
I want you to make a tape and loop it
so that it runs over and over, OK?

1429
01:23:09,316 --> 01:23:11,068
All right, run it. Run it!

1430
01:23:11,156 --> 01:23:12,145
All right.

1431
01:23:12,236 --> 01:23:13,908
Tape's rolling.

1432
01:23:13,996 --> 01:23:16,226
(TV) We still have no live picture,...

1433
01:23:16,316 --> 01:23:19,626
..but reports are
that the bus continues to circle...

1434
01:23:19,716 --> 01:23:21,832
(toilet flushes)

1435
01:23:21,916 --> 01:23:24,225
Everyone is safe for the moment.

1436
01:23:24,316 --> 01:23:28,229
Hard to imagine what's going
through their thoughts at this time.

1437
01:23:28,316 --> 01:23:30,068
Certainly, a sense of community...

1438
01:23:46,996 --> 01:23:50,545
Rig the steering wheel and the gas pedal.

1439
01:23:52,876 --> 01:23:55,470
All right, let's get them off.

1440
01:23:55,556 --> 01:23:57,512
OK, you, you, and you.

1441
01:23:58,716 --> 01:24:01,105
(TV) Police have just issued
a general statement,...

1442
01:24:01,196 --> 01:24:03,585
..which really doesn't tell us much more...

1443
01:24:03,676 --> 01:24:06,986
Grab my wrist. That's it. Good.

1444
01:24:07,076 --> 01:24:09,465
Come on. Look straight ahead.

1445
01:24:18,556 --> 01:24:19,591
Come on.

1446
01:24:22,316 --> 01:24:25,308
(TV) The bomber snuck in here
late last night...

1447
01:24:25,396 --> 01:24:26,351
Come on.

1448
01:24:26,436 --> 01:24:27,710
It's OK.

1449
01:24:27,796 --> 01:24:29,707
That's good, that's good.

1450
01:24:29,796 --> 01:24:31,024
Grab my wrist.

1451
01:24:31,116 --> 01:24:33,232
Take his hand.

1452
01:24:33,316 --> 01:24:35,307
That's it. Come on.

1453
01:24:40,156 --> 01:24:40,793
Let's go.

1454
01:24:45,156 --> 01:24:47,192
Come on, buddy. I got ya.

1455
01:24:47,276 --> 01:24:49,995
Give me your hand. Your hand.

1456
01:24:50,076 --> 01:24:51,634
Hold on. Hold on.

1457
01:24:51,716 --> 01:24:53,547
Grab my hand.

1458
01:24:53,636 --> 01:24:54,432
Don't look down.

1459
01:24:57,076 --> 01:24:57,872
Shit!

1460
01:24:59,076 --> 01:25:00,111
Jack!

1461
01:25:03,396 --> 01:25:04,715
Grab my hand!

1462
01:25:05,116 --> 01:25:06,310
Grab my hand!

1463
01:25:13,476 --> 01:25:16,149
Jack, I can't hold this any more.

1464
01:25:16,996 --> 01:25:19,829
Annie! You... hold on!

1465
01:25:22,796 --> 01:25:24,468
No, no!

1466
01:25:24,556 --> 01:25:25,511
No!

1467
01:25:27,236 --> 01:25:28,828
Hold it.

1468
01:25:35,596 --> 01:25:36,585
Oh, God.

1469
01:25:36,676 --> 01:25:39,144
Wedge down the gas pedal.

1470
01:25:41,956 --> 01:25:43,275
OK, I got it.

1471
01:25:54,636 --> 01:25:55,352
You got it?

1472
01:25:55,436 --> 01:25:56,312
Yeah.

1473
01:26:03,116 --> 01:26:04,549
I got it. OK

1474
01:26:04,996 --> 01:26:06,395
OK, Annie, get on.

1475
01:26:06,476 --> 01:26:07,033
Oh, God.

1476
01:26:07,116 --> 01:26:08,549
Jack, I can't do this.

1477
01:26:09,636 --> 01:26:10,512
Let's go!

1478
01:26:10,596 --> 01:26:11,915
Shit.

1479
01:26:11,996 --> 01:26:12,906
Shit, shit.

1480
01:26:14,436 --> 01:26:15,186
Jack.

1481
01:26:15,276 --> 01:26:16,311
Shit!

1482
01:26:17,836 --> 01:26:19,349
Hold on.

1483
01:27:40,916 --> 01:27:42,110
Shit!

1484
01:27:44,156 --> 01:27:46,272
(sirens approaching)

1485
01:27:49,796 --> 01:27:51,832
Are you all right?

1486
01:27:51,916 --> 01:27:53,713
No.

1487
01:27:55,116 --> 01:27:56,629
It's OK.

1488
01:27:56,716 --> 01:27:58,308
It's OK. It's over.

1489
01:27:58,396 --> 01:28:00,990
It's over. You did it.

1490
01:28:01,076 --> 01:28:02,794
You did it.

1491
01:28:07,196 --> 01:28:09,027
Oh, I hate the airport.

1492
01:28:14,436 --> 01:28:17,314
You're not going to get mushy on me,
are you?

1493
01:28:18,916 --> 01:28:20,315
Maybe.

1494
01:28:20,396 --> 01:28:22,148
I think I might.

1495
01:28:24,396 --> 01:28:28,833
I hope not because relationships that start
under intense circumstances never last.

1496
01:28:28,916 --> 01:28:29,428
Oh, yeah?

1497
01:28:29,516 --> 01:28:31,029
Yeah.
They've done extensive studying on this.

1498
01:28:32,916 --> 01:28:34,872
Here comes the cavalry.

1499
01:28:49,716 --> 01:28:51,513
How ya doing?

1500
01:28:51,596 --> 01:28:53,109
We're OK.

1501
01:28:53,796 --> 01:28:55,388
I just might be a nice guy...

1502
01:28:55,476 --> 01:28:57,034
...and let you have the rest of the day off.

1503
01:28:58,236 --> 01:28:59,112
Oh, boy.

1504
01:28:59,196 --> 01:29:02,632
Mac, this is Annie.

1505
01:29:02,716 --> 01:29:05,469
Annie, meet Lieutenant McMahon.

1506
01:29:05,556 --> 01:29:06,511
How you doing?

1507
01:29:06,596 --> 01:29:08,154
OK.

1508
01:29:08,396 --> 01:29:09,829
This should take care of it.

1509
01:29:09,916 --> 01:29:11,235
Ow!

1510
01:29:11,316 --> 01:29:12,226
Watch it.

1511
01:29:12,316 --> 01:29:13,510
Sorry.

1512
01:29:13,596 --> 01:29:16,793
We're going to take you guys back
and have you checked out.

1513
01:29:16,876 --> 01:29:17,831
Lieutenant!

1514
01:29:19,396 --> 01:29:20,146
It's him.

1515
01:29:20,236 --> 01:29:22,067
He wants to know
when he's gonna get his money.

1516
01:29:22,156 --> 01:29:25,626
Son of a bitch. I'll tell him
what to do with his goddamn money.

1517
01:29:25,716 --> 01:29:28,105
He doesn't know it blew up.

1518
01:29:29,916 --> 01:29:32,032
30 minutes.

1519
01:30:09,996 --> 01:30:11,588
I'll be right back.

1520
01:30:15,356 --> 01:30:17,153
All right, here's our target. Fox!

1521
01:30:17,236 --> 01:30:18,271
Yes, sir!

1522
01:30:18,356 --> 01:30:19,914
I want you in 4-1, you in 1-2. You're in 3.

1523
01:30:19,996 --> 01:30:20,985
Let's move it.

1524
01:30:21,076 --> 01:30:23,306
Are you sure the paint bomb
is in with the money?

1525
01:30:23,396 --> 01:30:24,226
It's done, sir.

1526
01:31:20,876 --> 01:31:24,232
Too bad, Jack.
You could've made a good cop.

1527
01:31:24,316 --> 01:31:26,910
(TV) The SWATvan
followed the bus to the airport.

1528
01:31:26,996 --> 01:31:28,634
OK.

1529
01:31:28,716 --> 01:31:31,276
We'll report across the landing field
when we're set up.

1530
01:31:31,356 --> 01:31:32,391
We still have no live picture.

1531
01:31:32,476 --> 01:31:35,513
Reports are that the bus
continues to circle...

1532
01:31:35,596 --> 01:31:37,154
...inside LAX.

1533
01:31:37,236 --> 01:31:38,635
...potentially a disastrous situation.

1534
01:31:38,716 --> 01:31:41,708
It's definitely been defused to some extent.

1535
01:31:44,596 --> 01:31:45,346
No!

1536
01:31:45,716 --> 01:31:47,274
No!

1537
01:32:10,196 --> 01:32:10,833
Miss.

1538
01:32:10,916 --> 01:32:11,348
Hmm?

1539
01:32:11,436 --> 01:32:13,154
You can't be this close.
You need to move back.

1540
01:32:13,236 --> 01:32:14,635
No. Jack Traven said...

1541
01:32:14,716 --> 01:32:17,833
Jack Traven asked
that you be brought out of harm's way.

1542
01:32:17,916 --> 01:32:18,905
Just move right over here.

1543
01:32:18,996 --> 01:32:21,066
He's running a little late.

1544
01:32:21,156 --> 01:32:23,624
He's not late.

1545
01:32:23,716 --> 01:32:24,865
What?

1546
01:32:24,956 --> 01:32:26,309
He's never late.

1547
01:32:26,396 --> 01:32:28,785
Well, that money hasn't moved.

1548
01:32:28,876 --> 01:32:31,151
We got 200 eyes on that can,...

1549
01:32:31,236 --> 01:32:33,352
...a bird dog in the bag.
I'd say he's covered.

1550
01:32:38,716 --> 01:32:39,671
Turn it on.

1551
01:32:39,756 --> 01:32:41,428
What for? It hasn't moved.

1552
01:32:41,516 --> 01:32:42,392
Just do it.

1553
01:32:45,596 --> 01:32:47,746
(beeping)

1554
01:32:49,796 --> 01:32:51,115
Shit. It's moving.

1555
01:32:51,196 --> 01:32:52,470
He's got the money.

1556
01:32:52,556 --> 01:32:53,466
Jack!

1557
01:33:03,316 --> 01:33:04,635
Shit!

1558
01:33:21,956 --> 01:33:22,593
Freeze!

1559
01:33:23,396 --> 01:33:24,306
Pop quiz,..

1560
01:33:24,396 --> 01:33:25,511
..asshole.

1561
01:33:25,596 --> 01:33:27,746
You have a hair trigger aimed at your head.

1562
01:33:27,836 --> 01:33:29,349
What do you do?

1563
01:33:29,876 --> 01:33:31,707
What do you do?

1564
01:33:31,796 --> 01:33:33,514
Turn around.

1565
01:33:34,156 --> 01:33:36,306
Turn around!

1566
01:33:54,356 --> 01:33:55,835
Oh, no.

1567
01:33:55,916 --> 01:33:57,588
I'm sorry.

1568
01:33:59,756 --> 01:34:00,984
Be prepared.

1569
01:34:01,076 --> 01:34:03,544
It's the boy Scout marching song.

1570
01:34:03,636 --> 01:34:05,433
What are you gonna do, Jack?

1571
01:34:05,516 --> 01:34:07,791
I don't think you can shoot her.

1572
01:34:08,556 --> 01:34:09,705
Let her go.

1573
01:34:11,116 --> 01:34:13,949
No, I don't think I'm gonna do that.

1574
01:34:14,036 --> 01:34:15,355
Fill it.

1575
01:34:15,436 --> 01:34:16,915
Now.

1576
01:34:19,756 --> 01:34:22,589
Well, I think Harry
would be very disappointed,...

1577
01:34:22,676 --> 01:34:24,314
...feeling that we're right back
where we started.

1578
01:34:24,836 --> 01:34:27,145
Let her go.
You don't need her. You have the money.

1579
01:34:27,236 --> 01:34:29,670
Take it and walk. Come on.

1580
01:34:29,756 --> 01:34:32,270
Just take it and walk. You don't need her.

1581
01:34:32,356 --> 01:34:34,426
Just take your goddamn money and walk!

1582
01:34:34,516 --> 01:34:38,191
Stay right there. I'll do it. I'll let go.

1583
01:34:38,276 --> 01:34:40,153
I'll let go. Oh, yeah.

1584
01:34:40,236 --> 01:34:42,989
You still don't get it. Do you, Jack?

1585
01:34:43,076 --> 01:34:45,067
Huh? The beauty of it.

1586
01:34:45,156 --> 01:34:48,228
A bomb is made to explode.

1587
01:34:48,956 --> 01:34:50,594
That's its meaning, its purpose.

1588
01:34:50,676 --> 01:34:53,349
Your life is empty because you spend it...

1589
01:34:53,436 --> 01:34:56,872
...trying to stop the bomb from becoming.

1590
01:34:56,956 --> 01:34:59,629
And for who? For what?

1591
01:34:59,716 --> 01:35:02,833
Do you know what a bomb is, Jack,...

1592
01:35:02,916 --> 01:35:04,190
...that doesn't explode?

1593
01:35:04,276 --> 01:35:06,346
It is a cheap gold watch, buddy.

1594
01:35:08,516 --> 01:35:09,551
You're crazy.

1595
01:35:09,676 --> 01:35:11,189
You're fucking crazy.

1596
01:35:12,316 --> 01:35:13,590
Oh, no.

1597
01:35:13,676 --> 01:35:15,632
Poor people are crazy, Jack.

1598
01:35:15,716 --> 01:35:17,434
I'm eccentric.

1599
01:35:17,516 --> 01:35:18,790
Get the money. Let's go.

1600
01:35:18,876 --> 01:35:20,912
Come on! Let's go! Move it! Move it!

1601
01:35:20,996 --> 01:35:22,588
You stay! Move it!

1602
01:35:22,676 --> 01:35:23,188
Move it!

1603
01:35:23,276 --> 01:35:24,231
In the door.

1604
01:35:24,876 --> 01:35:26,275
In that door! Now!

1605
01:35:27,636 --> 01:35:29,433
Bye, Jack.

1606
01:35:29,876 --> 01:35:30,353
Punk.

1607
01:35:31,436 --> 01:35:32,630
(people screaming)

1608
01:35:32,716 --> 01:35:33,751
(shouting)

1609
01:35:33,836 --> 01:35:35,428
All right!

1610
01:35:37,156 --> 01:35:38,430
Get in there.

1611
01:35:38,516 --> 01:35:39,073
Go on.

1612
01:35:39,156 --> 01:35:40,430
Get in.

1613
01:35:41,156 --> 01:35:42,350
You get back in there!

1614
01:35:42,436 --> 01:35:44,996
You get this train moving! Go on!

1615
01:35:45,076 --> 01:35:46,555
Are these seats taken?

1616
01:35:47,956 --> 01:35:49,025
No. Go.

1617
01:35:49,116 --> 01:35:51,949
All aboard. Doors will be closing.

1618
01:35:52,036 --> 01:35:54,345
Come on. Back over here.
Hands around the pole.

1619
01:35:54,436 --> 01:35:56,904
All aboard. Doors will be closing.

1620
01:36:14,596 --> 01:36:15,108
No!

1621
01:36:15,196 --> 01:36:16,390
Damn.

1622
01:36:35,276 --> 01:36:37,153
Come on. Come on. Come on.

1623
01:36:42,836 --> 01:36:44,667
Please report, Westbound 501.

1624
01:36:44,756 --> 01:36:45,905
What is your position?

1625
01:36:50,596 --> 01:36:53,394
Westbound 501, please check in.

1626
01:36:53,476 --> 01:36:55,671
Westbound 501.

1627
01:36:57,676 --> 01:36:59,792
We have police orders
to return to the station.

1628
01:36:59,876 --> 01:37:00,911
Do you copy?

1629
01:37:00,996 --> 01:37:01,872
You have to hold this.

1630
01:37:01,956 --> 01:37:04,868
It's like a grenade.
You have to help me now. Come on, hold it.

1631
01:37:04,956 --> 01:37:05,866
Don't let it go.

1632
01:37:06,356 --> 01:37:07,345
Huh?

1633
01:37:07,436 --> 01:37:08,391
I'm counting on you.

1634
01:37:08,476 --> 01:37:09,226
